parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seatbelt can cause the seatbelt to stick or malfunction, leading to a safety hazard in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt sticks or malfunctions
the seatbelt retractor does not extract the webbing properly
the seatbelt buckle does not buckle
the seatbelt will not retract
the seatbelt will not stay fastened
the seatbelt warning light illuminates
the seatbelt becomes stuck in the middle position
the seatbelt cable is twisted inside the housing
the seatbelt motor fails
the seatbelt retractor comes off the track
the seatbelt cable sticks out of the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to a safety hazard in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor does not extract the webbing properly
the seatbelt retractor comes off the track
the seatbelt cable is twisted inside the housing
the seatbelt retractor wears through due to a plastic cable
the seatbelt retractor fails to release
the seatbelt retractor sticks or locks up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt module can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to a safety hazard in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt module fails
the seatbelt sensors are not replaced
the seatbelt module is defective
the seatbelt fuel cell is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil springs can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to surrounding components.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the front of the vehicle
front wheels move uncontrollably
front coil springs fracture continuously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inoperative automatic seat belts can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Both front driver and passenger side automatic seat belts are inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Upper and Lower Ball Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn-out upper and lower ball joints can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to surrounding components.
symptoms: Loud noise coming from the front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to address recall issues can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: Dealership or manufacturer fails to repair or replace recalled components
despite the presence of a recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Steering Column Ignition Malfunction)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system in the steering column can cause sparks, smoke, and an abnormal burning odor, which can lead to a fire hazard and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Abnormal burning odor
sparks coming from the steering column near the ignition
white smoke coming from the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition System Failure (No Spark to Plugs)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls without warning
no sparks coming from the distributor to the plugs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Flooding and Fuel Injector Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine flooding can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to loss of control and potential accidents. Additionally, repeated flooding can cause damage to the engine and fuel system.
symptoms: Engine flooding
need to remove the 30 amp fuse for fuel injectors to stop the flood
replaced the fuse and started again.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Computer Malfunction (Engine Cut-Off and Loss of Power Steering)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the computer system can cause the engine to cut off, leading to loss of power steering and other vehicle components, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine cuts off
loss of power steering
loss of other vehicle components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to perform sluggishly, leading to reduced performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle performs sluggishly
battery replaced.
